    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Mechanism | Add Slide-Joint</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Add Slide-Joint</para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Terminology</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="4" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:247px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box-Elements" style="text-align:right;"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Technical Definition: Prismatic Joint</text> :</para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">A joint that only allows relative <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-Rectilinear-Translation">rectilinear translation</link>motion between two <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Parts</text> (rigid bodies).</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:247px;">
          <para styleclass="Element" style="text-align:right;"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">MechDesigner definition</text><text styleclass="Popup Box"> : </text><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Slide-Joint : </text></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">A joint, between two <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Parts</text>, that forces a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Line</text> in one <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text> to be collinear with a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Line</text> in the other <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text>. </para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:247px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box2" style="text-align:right;"><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Line : </text></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Line</text> is between two <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Points</text> that are on the <text styleclass="Popup Box2">Mechanism-Plane</text>, in one <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2" style="width:450px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box2"><text styleclass="Popup Box">The </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small">XY-Plane</text><text styleclass="Popup Box"> of </text><text styleclass="Interface">all</text><text styleclass="Popup Box">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Parts</text><text styleclass="Popup Box"> (and the </text><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Base-Part</text><text styleclass="Popup Box">) in a </text>Mechanism-Editor<text styleclass="Popup Box"> are coplanar with the </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Mechanism-Plane</text><text styleclass="Popup Box">.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">What is a Slide-Joint</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text style="font-style:normal;">A</text>&#32;<text styleclass="Element">Slide-Joint</text> makes a <text styleclass="Element">Line</text> in a <text styleclass="Element">Part</text> become collinear with a <text styleclass="Element">Line</text> in a different <text styleclass="Element">Part</text>. </para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">The two(2) <text styleclass="Element">Parts</text> can only slide relative to each other, the collinear <text styleclass="Element">Lines</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> being the sliding axis.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">A Slide-Joint</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="2" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:240px;">
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="MD-GA-SlideJointUndefined.png" scale="-99.90%" figurelistinclude="0"><caption><![CDATA[Slide-Joint]]></caption></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Slide-Joint in the graphic-area:</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Block" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td>
                <para styleclass="Body Table"><image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" figurelistinclude="0"></image>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">Narrow Rectangular Box</text> - equal to the length of the <text styleclass="Element">Line</text> that you select for the <text styleclass="Element">Slide-Joint </text>in one of the Parts.</para>
                <para styleclass="Body Table"><image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">&#32;</text><text styleclass="VariableName">Wide Rectangular Box</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"> - equal length to that of the </text><text styleclass="Element">Line</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"> that you select for the </text><text styleclass="Element">Slide-Joint </text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">in the other Part.</text></para>
                <para styleclass="Body Table"><image src="Red-14-3.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">&#32;</text><text styleclass="VariableName">Arrowhead</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"> - the </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Positive-Direction</text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT">*</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"> of the </text><text styleclass="Element">Slide-Joint</text></para>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="VariableName-IT">* </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Positive-direction</text><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered"> is important if you add to the </text><text styleclass="Element">Slide-Joint</text><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered"> a </text><text styleclass="Element">Motion-Dimension FB,</text> or it is the <text styleclass="Interface">Sliding-Part</text> in a <text styleclass="Element">Rack</text> in a <text styleclass="Element">Rack-Pinion</text>&#32;</para>
          <para styleclass="SeeAlso">See <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Command-FB-Motion-Dimension" anchor="SliderMotionDirection">Positive direction of Slide-Joints and Motion-Dimension</link></para>
          <para styleclass="SeeAlso"></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">IMPORTANT</text><text styleclass="Body Text CAP-ITALICS" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;">: </text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT">To calculate reaction forces for a Slide-Joint:</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">The <text styleclass="VariableName-IT">length and position</text> of the <text styleclass="Element">Lines</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> that define the </text><text styleclass="Element">Slide-Joint</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> must be </text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT">equivalent to actual design</text><text styleclass="Body Text">. </text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
